                                <div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane fade in active show" id="Coriander-section1">
                                    <p>The crop is suited for a temperature range of 17-27 degrees Celsius. It is best sown in pots directly rather than seed trays and then transplanting the sprout.</p>
                                </div>
                                <div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane fade" id="Coriander-section2">
                                    <p>Grow the plant in an area that is well light by sunlight and the soil has a pH of 6.2-6.8. Sow the seeds around half to an inch deep in the soil. Space out the seeds with a gap of 6 inches approximately, press soil over the seed, and cover it with a layer of mulch which is half an inch deep. Water well.</p>
                                </div>
                                <div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane fade" id="Coriander-section3">
                                    <p>The plant needs to be watered properly but be careful as overwatering can lead to root rot, hence good soil drainage is important as coriander has deep roots.</p>
                                </div>
                                <div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane fade" id="Coriander-section4">
                                    <p>The process of germination takes 2-3 weeks. To allow the plant to grow to their full size remember to thin young plants to 20cm apart. To extend the harvest, regularly snip soft stems while rotating the plant.</p>
                                </div>
